Understanding the ROI or Return on Investment of solving specific problems is critical.

2
00:00:06,945 --> 00:00:08,730
As I've mentioned before,

3
00:00:08,730 --> 00:00:12,570
there's an infinite number of problems that you and the team can be solving.

4
00:00:12,570 --> 00:00:15,645
But there's only so many hours in the day.

5
00:00:15,645 --> 00:00:20,400
Understanding and calculating ROI for different problems will help you to

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:25,380
understand where to focus your team's time in order to have the biggest impact.

7
00:00:25,380 --> 00:00:29,905
ROI is a way to measure the efficiency of an investment,

8
00:00:29,905 --> 00:00:33,020
like deciding to build a new product or feature.

9
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
In a mathematical sense,

10
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:40,150
it's the amount gained minus the amount spent divided by the amount spent.

11
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:43,775
Amount gained doesn't just have to be an increase in sales,

12
00:00:43,775 --> 00:00:46,210
but it could also be cost savings.

13
00:00:46,210 --> 00:00:48,740
You just want to make sure that you get

14
00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:51,935
the impact into something that can be measured in dollars.

15
00:00:51,935 --> 00:00:54,455
Keep in mind that these are just estimates,

16
00:00:54,455 --> 00:00:58,324
and they can get pretty complicated when you start adding in lots of factors.

17
00:00:58,324 --> 00:01:00,980
You should work with someone on the finance team or

18
00:01:00,980 --> 00:01:04,100
the data science team to help build this out in more detail.

19
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:07,745
One thing that is important is that the higher the ROI is,

20
00:01:07,745 --> 00:01:09,545
the better the business outcome.

21
00:01:09,545 --> 00:01:16,160
This is because high ROI means that you're able to create more impact with less effort.

22
